{"cursor":"3464","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox Former Country |conventional_long_name = Kingdom of Hejaz |native_name\n= |common_name = Hejaz |continent = Asia |status = |status_text = |p1 = Hejaz\nVilayet |flag_p1 = Flag of the Ottoman Empire.svg |s1 = Kingdom of Nejd and\nHejaz |flag_s1 = Flag of Hejaz 1926.svg |s2 = Transjordan |flag_s2 = Flag of\nJordan.svg |image_flag = Flag of Hejaz 1917.svg |flag_type = Flag of Hejaz\n(1917) |image_coat = Flag of Hejaz 1920.svg |symbol_type = Flag of Hejaz (1920)\n|coa_size = 120px |image_map = Hijaz.png |image_map_caption = Kingdom of Hejaz\n(green) and present Hejaz region (red) on the Arabian Peninsula. |capital =\nMecca |common_languages = ArabicPersian Ottoman Turkish |religion = Islam\n|government_type = Absolute monarchy |title_leader = [[Sharif of Mecca|Sharif]]\n|leader1 = Hussein bin Ali |year_leader1 = 1916–1924 |leader2 = Ali bin\nHussein |year_leader2 = 1924–1925 |legislature = |era = Interwar period\n|event_start = Kingdom established |date_start = 10 June |year_start = 1916\n|event1 = Recognized |date_event1 = 10 August 1920 |event_end = Conquered by\nNejd |date_end = 19 December |year_end = 1925 |event_post = Ibn Saud crowned\nKing of Hejaz |date_post = 8 January 1926\n\n|stat_year1 = 1920 |stat_area1 = |stat_pop1 = 850000 }}\n\nThe 'Kingdom of Hejaz' was a state in the Hejaz region ruled by the Hashemite\nfamily. It became independent from the collapsing Ottoman Empire as a result of\nWorld War I when the Sharif of Mecca made a deal with the British that the Arab\npopulation would be instigated to revolt against the Turks in exchange for a\nunified Arab country. In 1916, the Sharif of Mecca declared himself King of\nHejaz as his Sharifian Army participated with other Arab forces and the British\nEmpire in expelling the Turks from the Arabian peninsula.\n\nThe Hejaz region had some strategic infrastructure, particularly the Hejaz\nrailway, which was put out of operation in the 